- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cut elimination in sequent calculi for propositional modal logics, which is a topic within mathematical logic and computer science. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a criterion for cut elimination in modal logics, which is relevant to the development of automated reasoning systems in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper deals with the development of a general criterion for cut elimination, which could potentially be applied to machine learning algorithms. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a criterion for cut elimination in sequent calculi, which is relevant to the design and implementation of programming languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the fully internalised calculi obtained for various conditional logics.
